2
00:03:02,916 --> 00:03:04,474
We managed to put Chu Tu behind bars

3
00:03:05,051 --> 00:03:07,212
but the operation was a costly one.

4
00:03:08,388 --> 00:03:09,946
You destroyed the squatter village

5
00:03:10,357 --> 00:03:12,518
and the Government
had to rehouse the families.

6
00:03:12,726 --> 00:03:14,057
and pay the redemption

7
00:03:14,694 --> 00:03:15,718
Last time' during the operation

8
00:03:16,162 --> 00:03:17,561
You damaged the shopping centre as well.

9
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:20,556
We paid over a million
for the chandelier alone.

10
00:03:33,546 --> 00:03:34,535
But the taxpayers know

11
00:03:34,714 --> 00:03:36,579
police work doesn't come cheaply.

12
00:03:36,850 --> 00:03:37,839
But they don't expect to pay for

13
00:03:38,184 --> 00:03:40,675
the cost of someone's heroism.

14
00:03:41,821 --> 00:03:44,585
Why didn't you use the stairs?
Did you have to destroy that chandelier?

15
00:03:45,492 --> 00:03:47,392
Do you always have to be different?

16
00:04:19,693 --> 00:04:23,151
You're right.
This force doesn't need superstars.

17
00:04:23,663 --> 00:04:25,028
We need disciplined policemen.

18
00:04:28,034 --> 00:04:29,899
l wasn't expecting a promotion.

19
00:04:30,170 --> 00:04:33,139
Ka-kui' the operation
succeeded through team effort'

20
00:04:33,406 --> 00:04:34,839
not just because of you.

21
00:04:35,508 --> 00:04:38,306
You should be grateful
that we didn't fire you.

22
00:04:38,812 --> 00:04:41,337
And the bosses wanted you disciplined

23
00:04:41,614 --> 00:04:42,876
for holding me as hostage.

24
00:04:43,817 --> 00:04:45,751
l managed to talk them out of it.

25
00:04:46,252 --> 00:04:47,310
l'm very grateful.

26
00:05:08,008 --> 00:05:09,908
l worry about your individualism'

27
00:05:10,110 --> 00:05:11,771
you're just a police officer.
Don't forget the point.

28
00:05:12,712 --> 00:05:15,203
As of today' you're back in uniform.

29
00:05:16,149 --> 00:05:17,741
You'll be assigned where needed.

30
00:05:18,885 --> 00:05:19,977
You mean he'll be an errand boy?!

31
00:05:22,722 --> 00:05:23,746
l think you'll be very busy.

32
00:05:32,732 --> 00:05:35,064
What else do you do apart
from giving out tickets?

33
00:05:55,522 --> 00:05:56,546
Calling all units'

34
00:05:56,856 --> 00:05:59,324
there's been a serious road accident
at the lndustrial Park.

35
00:05:59,592 --> 00:06:00,684
Traffic is brought to a standstill.

36
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:02,654
All units in the area please respond.

37
00:07:07,494 --> 00:07:09,621
May' go home.
l'm working now.

38
00:07:09,863 --> 00:07:11,091
Just think of me

39
00:07:11,397 --> 00:07:12,489
as a member of the public.

40
00:07:12,832 --> 00:07:15,494
And l want to talk to a policeman.

41
00:07:15,735 --> 00:07:16,724
About what?

42
00:07:17,170 --> 00:07:19,434
l think you look very smart in a uniform.

43
00:07:20,974 --> 00:07:22,669
Stop it' l'm on duty.

44
00:07:22,842 --> 00:07:23,831
l've brought you a cold drink.

45
00:07:31,217 --> 00:07:32,707
Thank you.

46
00:07:32,919 --> 00:07:35,513
Thank you' sir.

47
00:07:51,571 --> 00:07:52,560
l can't drink here.

48
00:07:52,605 --> 00:07:54,402
Go on' you need a break.

49
00:07:54,541 --> 00:07:55,530
lf l have a drink'

50
00:07:55,575 --> 00:07:56,769
l'll need the toilet soon.

51
00:07:57,110 --> 00:07:58,099
Come on.

52
00:07:58,778 --> 00:08:00,609
May' l'll get into trouble.

53
00:08:02,949 --> 00:08:05,884
Hello' superhero!
You still haven't been sacked?!

54
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:08,987
You're lucky you're not in jail with Chu.

55
00:08:09,289 --> 00:08:10,278
You think so?

56
00:08:17,130 --> 00:08:18,529
The doctors said

57
00:08:18,665 --> 00:08:20,189
l only had three months to live.

58
00:08:20,934 --> 00:08:22,697
lt's called compassionate release.

59
00:08:23,403 --> 00:08:26,429
Three months can pass quickly' very quickly.

60
00:08:27,207 --> 00:08:30,904
My boss will be alive long after you're dead.

61
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:34,579
Don't you know you're threatening him?

62
00:08:34,814 --> 00:08:37,647
Really? ln that case' he can sue me.

63
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:39,010
Just be careful!

64
00:08:39,152 --> 00:08:40,141
Drive on.

65
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:45,846
Ka-kui?

66
00:09:13,586 --> 00:09:14,951
Ka-Kui' Chu Tu is out from Jail.

67
00:09:15,255 --> 00:09:16,244
l know' so?

68
00:09:16,556 --> 00:09:17,545
You already knew? That's good then.

69
00:09:17,590 --> 00:09:19,820
As a police
who wouldn't have caught a thief?

70
00:09:20,059 --> 00:09:21,048
Who would you be scare of?

71
00:09:21,094 --> 00:09:21,992
Just remember'

72
00:09:22,028 --> 00:09:24,223
there are 250'000 Royal HK Police
at your back up.

73
00:09:25,398 --> 00:09:28,060
Bill' are there really 250'000 police in HK?

74
00:09:28,434 --> 00:09:29,731
Just because wer
are still recruiting new blood.

75
00:09:29,936 --> 00:09:30,925
Didn't you notice newspaper ad?

76
00:09:32,238 --> 00:09:33,227
What are you waiting for?

77
00:09:33,273 --> 00:09:34,262
Go on patrol!

78
00:09:37,010 --> 00:09:38,375
Hey' l've talked to Raymond.

79
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:39,704
He said you could carry a gun
even after work.

80
00:09:48,388 --> 00:09:49,377
l'm very happy tonight.

81
00:09:49,789 --> 00:09:51,882
The show and dinner were great.

82
00:09:52,292 --> 00:09:53,987
But you don't seem very happy.

83
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:55,184
Really? l am happy.

84
00:09:57,630 --> 00:09:59,723
l wish you had enjoyed it
as much as l did.

85
00:10:02,268 --> 00:10:03,257
Are you worried about Chu?

86
00:10:03,369 --> 00:10:05,234
No. But l'm just being careful.

87
00:10:13,413 --> 00:10:14,402
Maybe next week...

88
00:10:14,447 --> 00:10:15,436
Hey' superhero!

89
00:10:17,383 --> 00:10:19,180
Off duty already?

90
00:10:19,352 --> 00:10:20,341
What are you doing here?

91
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:21,712
l can park here'

92
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:24,779
you can't give me a ticket.

93
00:10:25,358 --> 00:10:28,225
Yeah' you must have a nice view

94
00:10:28,494 --> 00:10:29,483
from flat B of the first floor.
Am l right?

95
00:10:30,363 --> 00:10:31,352
Go upstairs.

96
00:10:35,868 --> 00:10:36,857
How did you find this address?

97
00:10:38,404 --> 00:10:40,167
lt's amazing what information

98
00:10:40,773 --> 00:10:42,934
you can get with money.

99
00:10:43,242 --> 00:10:47,178
People will do anything for money'
you know?

100
00:10:47,814 --> 00:10:48,838
What do you mean?

101
00:10:49,015 --> 00:10:51,313
There's a narrow stairwell in the building.

102
00:10:51,651 --> 00:10:55,018
lf there was a fire' it'd spread

103
00:10:55,188 --> 00:10:56,883
rapidly through the building.

104
00:10:57,490 --> 00:10:59,754
Because of the narrow access'

105
00:11:00,026 --> 00:11:02,221
the fire brigade couldn't get in here.

106
00:11:02,428 --> 00:11:03,986
Therefore' you'd better

107
00:11:04,230 --> 00:11:05,663
keep a close eye on her.

108
00:11:07,066 --> 00:11:08,465
lf she were to get her pretty ass burnt'

109
00:11:08,634 --> 00:11:11,933
it'd ruin her marriage prospects.

110
00:11:12,105 --> 00:11:13,094
Bastard!

111
00:11:23,282 --> 00:11:25,944
Oh' hero' l'm so happy!

112
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:34,749
Sorry.

113
00:11:35,061 --> 00:11:36,790
lt'd my fault really.

114
00:11:37,263 --> 00:11:39,231
A police like me have lots of enemies
and you are threatened.

115
00:11:40,199 --> 00:11:41,291
l'm not scared.

116
00:11:41,768 --> 00:11:43,531
lf you don't have any enemies'

117
00:11:43,836 --> 00:11:46,236
that means you couldn't catch a thief.

118
00:11:47,373 --> 00:11:48,567
Could you rehouse yourself for a while?

119
00:11:49,275 --> 00:11:50,606
Don't worry about me.

120
00:11:50,777 --> 00:11:52,267
They are just morons.

121
00:11:52,578 --> 00:11:54,273
No. We could be noticed
so easily while they won't

122
00:11:55,214 --> 00:11:56,203
This way then'

123
00:11:56,249 --> 00:11:58,547
l'll move to my aunt's and hide for a while.

124
00:11:59,152 --> 00:12:00,141
Don't think about it too much.

125
00:12:00,753 --> 00:12:04,018
But' if you threw a vase onto him
then l'll be dead definitely.

126
00:12:19,872 --> 00:12:20,861
May.

127
00:12:22,008 --> 00:12:22,997
Auntie.

128
00:12:23,109 --> 00:12:25,270
You're on your own?
Where's Ka-kui?

129
00:12:25,478 --> 00:12:26,706
He's still on duty.

130
00:12:26,946 --> 00:12:28,345
lt's OK' l can manage.

131
00:12:28,681 --> 00:12:30,945
l'm not against you dating a policeman'

132
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:34,708
but l don't want him to spend
too much time on his work.

133
00:12:35,154 --> 00:12:36,143
He's stubborn' too.

134
00:12:36,189 --> 00:12:37,713
But he's a good policeman.

135
00:12:37,924 --> 00:12:39,983
That's why he has lots of enemies

136
00:12:40,193 --> 00:12:42,184
and you have to move home.

137
00:12:42,395 --> 00:12:43,794
l have to be careful.

138
00:12:44,063 --> 00:12:46,054
That way' he doesn't need to worry about me.

139
00:12:47,667 --> 00:12:49,396
He ought to worry about you.

140
00:12:50,236 --> 00:12:51,225
Who are they?

141
00:12:51,437 --> 00:12:52,426
lt was them last time.

142
00:12:53,239 --> 00:12:54,536
l guess superhero isn't here.

143
00:12:56,142 --> 00:12:57,404
Wait for me in the restaurant.

144
00:12:57,810 --> 00:12:58,799
Right.

145
00:12:58,845 --> 00:13:01,575
What do you want?
We have a score to settle.

146
00:13:01,814 --> 00:13:03,111
l just want to know

147
00:13:03,382 --> 00:13:05,009
where you're going.

148
00:13:05,184 --> 00:13:06,173
lt's nothing to do with her.

149
00:13:07,553 --> 00:13:11,045
You must be her mother. Am l right?

150
00:13:11,724 --> 00:13:12,713
Bastard!

151
00:13:12,758 --> 00:13:14,692
You call me a bastard?

152
00:13:14,961 --> 00:13:18,658
Yes! l'm the bastard son of a bastard!

153
00:13:19,031 --> 00:13:20,020
l'm not afraid of you.

154
00:13:20,066 --> 00:13:21,055
Come on.

155
00:13:21,634 --> 00:13:25,900
Auntie' why has your daughter
fallen for a cop?

156
00:13:26,138 --> 00:13:27,366
That could be dangerous.

157
00:13:27,607 --> 00:13:30,235
Living on the 19th floor
is dangerous' too.

158
00:13:30,476 --> 00:13:34,913
What if you fall when
you're cleaning the windows?

159
00:13:36,015 --> 00:13:37,004
Go ahead!

160
00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:40,641
Don't be silly.

161
00:13:42,555 --> 00:13:44,079
Go away.

162
00:13:44,590 --> 00:13:45,579
Off!

163
00:13:45,625 --> 00:13:46,853
You bastard.

164
00:13:47,193 --> 00:13:48,182
Don't grab my hair.

165
00:13:48,594 --> 00:13:49,925
You're hurting me.

166
00:13:50,196 --> 00:13:51,288
You bitch.

167
00:13:55,635 --> 00:13:57,227
Easy' she's just a girl.

168
00:13:57,537 --> 00:13:59,334
Think yourself lucky.
lf you were a man' you'd be dead.

169
00:13:59,639 --> 00:14:00,628
l won't forget this.

170
00:14:00,673 --> 00:14:02,140
Come on.

171
00:14:02,308 --> 00:14:03,502
You be careful!

172
00:14:05,011 --> 00:14:06,000
Are you ok?

173
00:14:15,688 --> 00:14:16,677
Auntie!

174
00:14:16,722 --> 00:14:18,986
lt's your job that brings the enemies here.

175
00:14:19,392 --> 00:14:20,586
Look' May was badly beaten because of you!

176
00:14:21,427 --> 00:14:22,758
l've told you not to be with him.

177
00:14:24,964 --> 00:14:26,022
Did John Ko attack you?

178
00:14:26,966 --> 00:14:28,797
l started hitting him first.

179
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:31,336
He just hit me back.

180
00:14:31,504 --> 00:14:33,028
And they knocked me down.

181
00:14:33,439 --> 00:14:36,772
My backside still hurts.
l can't sit down now.

182
00:14:36,943 --> 00:14:37,967
How did they know you'd be here?

183
00:14:38,744 --> 00:14:40,075
They followed her.

184
00:14:40,313 --> 00:14:41,678
That's how.

185
00:14:41,948 --> 00:14:44,109
They're watching us from across the street.

186
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:46,813
l wonder what's next.

187
00:14:48,254 --> 00:14:49,516
Ka-kui' don't!

188
00:14:49,855 --> 00:14:52,153
He should go and scold them.

189
00:14:52,658 --> 00:14:53,784
lf it's that simple'

190
00:14:54,327 --> 00:14:55,885
then l'll be relieved.

191
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:21,778
ldiolt! Are you crazy?

192
00:15:39,839 --> 00:15:41,431
What would you do beside bullying women?

193
00:15:42,041 --> 00:15:44,942
lt's my favourite hobby.

194
00:16:09,201 --> 00:16:10,190
Get the bastard!

195
00:17:24,076 --> 00:17:25,703
You know the law' don't you?!

196
00:17:25,945 --> 00:17:26,934
lf they did threaten her'

197
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:28,035
you could arrest them.

198
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:29,508
l don't care.

199
00:17:30,149 --> 00:17:31,241
l got carried away.

200
00:17:31,717 --> 00:17:33,082
That's not a good reason.

201
00:17:34,086 --> 00:17:35,917
He reacted like anyone else would.

202
00:17:36,155 --> 00:17:38,316
He's not anyone else.
He's a police officer.

203
00:17:38,624 --> 00:17:39,921
What you've done is disgraceful!

204
00:17:40,126 --> 00:17:41,115
lt has disgraced us the police.

205
00:17:41,160 --> 00:17:42,127
l don't think so.

206
00:17:42,161 --> 00:17:43,150
lf a policeman fails to respond to

207
00:17:43,329 --> 00:17:44,318
a personal threat'

208
00:17:44,463 --> 00:17:46,431
it's disgracefu.
And it disgraces the law' too.

209
00:17:46,632 --> 00:17:48,099
You're a show-off.

210
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:49,289
So we won't forget you arrested Chu.

211
00:17:49,568 --> 00:17:52,469
How can l explain this to the chief!

212
00:17:53,773 --> 00:17:55,673
You don't have to. l quit.

213
00:18:05,317 --> 00:18:07,285
You think that
will resolve the problem?

214
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:10,814
Why not?
This is probably the best solution.

215
00:18:12,491 --> 00:18:13,480
l'll leave now.

216
00:18:14,794 --> 00:18:18,059
Thank you for your support in the past.
Goodbye.

217
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:22,322
Ka-kui.

218
00:18:24,837 --> 00:18:25,826
lf that's your last word'

219
00:18:26,839 --> 00:18:29,967
then try to find a less stressful job.
Bye-bye.

220
00:18:31,243 --> 00:18:32,437
l will.

221
00:18:33,746 --> 00:18:35,976
You think you can do anything
because you're cops.

222
00:18:36,248 --> 00:18:37,237
Don't you know the law?!

223
00:18:37,349 --> 00:18:40,477
You can't beat me up just like that.
Kill me if you can.

224
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:42,481
Shut up and sign this.

225
00:18:42,788 --> 00:18:44,949
l'm not signing anything.
No way!

226
00:18:45,391 --> 00:18:48,224
l'll sue you for every penny
you've got.

227
00:18:48,494 --> 00:18:51,486
l've got lots of money.
l'll get a lawyer. l'll sue you!

228
00:18:57,169 --> 00:18:58,158
What?!

229
00:18:58,838 --> 00:18:59,827
No!

230
00:18:59,872 --> 00:19:03,000
See? You saw this officer
try to assault me.

231
00:19:03,275 --> 00:19:04,503
He wants to beat me up like before

232
00:19:04,810 --> 00:19:06,869
when he hit me and broke my glasses.

233
00:19:07,112 --> 00:19:09,046
You'll pay for that.

234
00:19:09,348 --> 00:19:11,213
You would dare to beat me up here?

235
00:19:11,717 --> 00:19:14,447
Come on. What are you waiting for?!

236
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:18,281
Come on. l'm going to sue you'
you're going to jail.

237
00:19:29,368 --> 00:19:31,165
These youngsters have no patience.

238
00:19:31,337 --> 00:19:33,601
Bill' why didn't you ask him to stay?

239
00:19:34,073 --> 00:19:35,062
You should have said so!

240
00:19:35,140 --> 00:19:36,664
l thought you meant
throw him out of here.

241
00:19:39,879 --> 00:19:42,575
Now l know what this gesture means'
l'll remember it.

242
00:19:48,053 --> 00:19:49,418
Ka-kui' what's the matter?

243
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:52,179
You don't want me to be a policeman' do you?

244
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:56,961
Of course l do' l'm proud of you.

245
00:19:57,563 --> 00:19:58,996
What do l have after being a cop

246
00:19:59,431 --> 00:20:01,058
for such a long time? Just enemies.

247
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:04,530
There you go!
That means you've done your job well.

248
00:20:04,737 --> 00:20:06,432
lf a cop has no enemies'
there is only one reason:

249
00:20:06,639 --> 00:20:07,628
he hasn't caught any crooks.

250
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:10,300
l'm glad they hate you!

251
00:20:10,576 --> 00:20:12,567
lt proves that you're a tough good cop.

252
00:20:13,112 --> 00:20:14,101
Thanks for that.

253
00:20:16,148 --> 00:20:17,638
But l've had enough.

254
00:20:18,350 --> 00:20:19,510
l resigned today.

255
00:20:19,551 --> 00:20:20,540
Really?

256
00:20:20,586 --> 00:20:21,518
Are you disappointed?

257
00:20:21,553 --> 00:20:22,542
You're really quitting?!

258
00:20:24,256 --> 00:20:26,417
l'm so happy!

259
00:20:27,126 --> 00:20:28,115
Calm down.

260
00:20:28,494 --> 00:20:30,018
What's she doing?!

261
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:37,194
May' for these years'
l haven't treat you as good as l should.

262
00:20:37,369 --> 00:20:38,358
lt's my fault.

263
00:20:38,504 --> 00:20:39,493
l have three months' holidays.

264
00:20:40,005 --> 00:20:41,097
Let's go somewhere else to relax!

265
00:20:41,674 --> 00:20:43,164
Ka-kui' you mean it?

266
00:20:43,943 --> 00:20:45,808
Where to go then? Bali.

267
00:20:45,844 --> 00:20:46,833
Good idea!

268
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:49,713
We haven't travel for years.

269
00:20:50,082 --> 00:20:51,777
Right' so let's go.

270
00:20:52,618 --> 00:20:55,280
lt feels good to fly on the plane.

271
00:21:00,793 --> 00:21:02,055
That's $5'540' please.

272
00:21:02,194 --> 00:21:03,183
Right.

273
00:21:05,898 --> 00:21:06,887
l'll see you outside.

274
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:09,632
Credit card?
Sure.

275
00:21:15,574 --> 00:21:17,337
Here's our catalogue' sir.

276
00:21:17,609 --> 00:21:18,837
Thank you. Bye.

277
00:21:26,318 --> 00:21:27,842
What clothes should l take?

278
00:21:27,987 --> 00:21:29,614
You won't need any in Bali.

279
00:21:29,822 --> 00:21:30,811
Don't be silly!

280
00:21:31,523 --> 00:21:33,457
l can't believe we're going.

281
00:21:33,659 --> 00:21:34,956
l just hope they won't rip us off.

282
00:21:35,361 --> 00:21:36,885
No' they're a big company.

283
00:21:37,096 --> 00:21:38,085
lt's trustworthy.

284
00:21:38,163 --> 00:21:39,687
lt's paid for now.

285
00:21:40,032 --> 00:21:41,226
Let's cross our fingers.

286
00:21:42,368 --> 00:21:44,359
Fey!
Ka-kui.

287
00:21:44,403 --> 00:21:45,392
ls this your area?

288
00:21:45,437 --> 00:21:46,597
Yes.
What's up?

289
00:21:46,638 --> 00:21:48,606
We've received a bomb threat
in here.

290
00:21:48,741 --> 00:21:49,730
Really?

291
00:21:49,775 --> 00:21:51,902
Yeah. Can you help us out?

292
00:21:54,546 --> 00:21:55,535
All right' then. Thanks.

293
00:21:56,015 --> 00:21:57,004
Ka-kui!

294
00:21:58,050 --> 00:21:59,381
l'll just take a look' all right?

295
00:22:00,619 --> 00:22:01,608
Sun.

296
00:22:02,054 --> 00:22:03,043
Just in time. What's up?

297
00:22:03,288 --> 00:22:05,119
We got a call about a bomb.

298
00:22:05,357 --> 00:22:06,449
Are you sure it's real?

299
00:22:07,426 --> 00:22:10,293
l don't think he was kidding.
He told us to clear the area.

300
00:22:10,496 --> 00:22:11,793
We have ten minutes.

301
00:22:12,197 --> 00:22:13,186
Really?

302
00:22:13,232 --> 00:22:15,359
The manager said he's nuts.

303
00:22:15,701 --> 00:22:18,670
Start clearing the building now.

304
00:22:19,438 --> 00:22:21,269
There are too many people.

305
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:23,408
lf it's a hoax' who'll be to blame?

306
00:22:23,642 --> 00:22:25,371
l'm used to getting an earful.

307
00:22:25,577 --> 00:22:27,841
lf it is real' we'll endanger lives.

308
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:29,674
That's true.
What do we do?

309
00:22:30,215 --> 00:22:33,378
Consider it real. Clear the building.
Call headquarters.

310
00:22:34,019 --> 00:22:35,008
Where's the fire alarm?

311
00:22:36,055 --> 00:22:37,044
Over there.

312
00:22:37,322 --> 00:22:38,311
Ka-kui.

313
00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:40,920
We'll go set off the fire alarm. Come on.

314
00:22:47,299 --> 00:22:48,596
Your truncheon. But...

315
00:22:48,734 --> 00:22:49,723
Come on' l'll bear the consquence.

316
00:22:53,806 --> 00:22:54,795
Follow me.

317
00:23:07,886 --> 00:23:09,080
Don't panic. Don't worry.

318
00:23:09,354 --> 00:23:12,084
Come back. l've opened the till already.

319
00:23:13,192 --> 00:23:14,181
Have they paid?

320
00:23:15,027 --> 00:23:16,961
What's going on?

321
00:23:22,234 --> 00:23:23,223
lt's nothing.

322
00:23:23,268 --> 00:23:25,828
What should we do?
They're not taking any notice.

323
00:23:26,004 --> 00:23:26,993
Ka-kui.

324
00:23:30,409 --> 00:23:31,774
Don't stay here. Go on!

325
00:23:32,111 --> 00:23:34,944
Your attention please'
evacuate the building.

326
00:23:35,214 --> 00:23:38,479
Everybody please leave immediately.

327
00:23:38,717 --> 00:23:40,651
There's a fire in the building.

328
00:23:40,986 --> 00:23:42,578
Please leave now.

329
00:23:45,090 --> 00:23:46,352
Please leave in an orderly manner.

330
00:23:46,959 --> 00:23:49,223
Everybody outside.

331
00:23:49,661 --> 00:23:50,650
Be careful.

332
00:23:57,369 --> 00:24:00,133
What's going on? Why the alarm's on?

333
00:24:01,073 --> 00:24:02,097
How about our business?

334
00:24:03,542 --> 00:24:05,339
Fay.
What's up?

335
00:24:05,377 --> 00:24:07,436
Get them out of here.

336
00:24:09,248 --> 00:24:11,876
This is for your own safety. Go now!

337
00:24:12,184 --> 00:24:13,674
What about you?

338
00:24:14,019 --> 00:24:15,077
l won't be long. You go first.

339
00:24:19,091 --> 00:24:20,149
Check the building.

340
00:24:36,808 --> 00:24:39,242
l can't understand this. lt's crazy!

341
00:24:45,083 --> 00:24:46,072
Who's in charge?

342
00:24:46,218 --> 00:24:47,207
You talk to them.

343
00:24:48,153 --> 00:24:51,145
Please leave here now'
the police will take care of it.

344
00:24:51,957 --> 00:24:53,515
Ka-kui. Ka-kui!

345
00:24:53,659 --> 00:24:55,820
l'm all right. You go home first.

346
00:25:02,201 --> 00:25:03,190
Hello' sir.

347
00:25:03,468 --> 00:25:04,457
Who made the call?

348
00:25:04,636 --> 00:25:06,467
We received a call

349
00:25:06,705 --> 00:25:08,002
but we didn't know if it was a hoax.

350
00:25:09,274 --> 00:25:10,263
Who set off the alarm?

351
00:25:12,010 --> 00:25:12,999
lt was me' sir.

352
00:25:14,546 --> 00:25:15,535
You may leave.

353
00:25:21,086 --> 00:25:22,314
Why did you do it?

354
00:25:22,721 --> 00:25:24,382
Sir' when l was in the Police Academy'

355
00:25:24,590 --> 00:25:25,579
l was taught that

356
00:25:25,791 --> 00:25:28,259
public safety comes first.

357
00:25:28,493 --> 00:25:29,482
So l set off the alarm.

358
00:25:29,628 --> 00:25:31,323
Do you think
you're indispensable?

359
00:25:33,265 --> 00:25:36,564
Superintendent. There's no fire.

360
00:25:36,969 --> 00:25:39,369
But it was your men
who cleared the building.

361
00:25:39,605 --> 00:25:42,096
Right. The Bomb Disposal Unit are coming.

362
00:25:42,341 --> 00:25:43,569
You won't be needed now.

363
00:25:43,809 --> 00:25:45,936
Right. l hope this isn't a hoax.

364
00:25:46,345 --> 00:25:47,437
Uncle Bill. So do l.

365
00:25:48,180 --> 00:25:50,171
Raymond. They want to see
the head man.

366
00:25:50,349 --> 00:25:51,748
Shall l go?

367
00:25:52,884 --> 00:25:55,045
Where's the Bomb Disposal Unit?
On their way.

368
00:25:59,024 --> 00:26:00,013
What a mess.

369
00:26:00,158 --> 00:26:01,182
Did l do the right thing?

370
00:26:01,927 --> 00:26:03,519
How do l do know? Don't ask me.

371
00:26:04,496 --> 00:26:05,690
Right now'

372
00:26:06,632 --> 00:26:08,623
we have to wait and see.

373
00:26:08,767 --> 00:26:09,756
Tell them to leave.

374
00:26:10,702 --> 00:26:11,930
You can go back in very soon.

375
00:26:12,838 --> 00:26:14,135
My ball!

376
00:26:38,063 --> 00:26:39,052
When can we go back in?

377
00:26:39,364 --> 00:26:40,353
Now what?

378
00:26:40,399 --> 00:26:41,161
Very soon.

379
00:26:41,199 --> 00:26:42,131
Here's your ball.

380
00:26:42,167 --> 00:26:43,156
Thank you.

381
00:26:49,875 --> 00:26:50,864
Ready?

382
00:26:50,909 --> 00:26:52,103
The Bomb Disposal Unit are here.

383
00:26:53,045 --> 00:26:54,774
lf they don't find anything'

384
00:26:56,181 --> 00:26:57,170
the boss will blow a fuse.

385
00:26:57,749 --> 00:26:59,239
Uncle Bill' l'm very sorry.

386
00:26:59,484 --> 00:27:01,179
l'm not...

387
00:27:14,966 --> 00:27:15,955
Red alert!

388
00:27:16,001 --> 00:27:16,990
All units move in.

389
00:27:17,703 --> 00:27:19,170
Go and fight the fire. Go on.

390
00:27:30,449 --> 00:27:33,213
l suppose the good news is
nobody got hurt.

391
00:27:33,385 --> 00:27:34,374
What are the losses?

392
00:27:34,920 --> 00:27:36,512
The insurance will cover it.

393
00:27:36,788 --> 00:27:39,382
l'm more worried about
the damage to our image.

394
00:27:39,825 --> 00:27:41,952
l've asked the press to cooperate
and l'm sure they will.

395
00:27:43,762 --> 00:27:46,230
But who did it and why our company?

396
00:27:46,865 --> 00:27:47,957
lt may not be against us.

397
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:50,995
lt could be someone
who's mentally disturbed.

398
00:27:54,106 --> 00:27:55,300
There's a man on the line' sir.

399
00:27:55,574 --> 00:27:56,973
He says he planted the bomb.

400
00:27:57,542 --> 00:27:58,531
Have it put through.

401
00:27:59,911 --> 00:28:00,900
Put him through.

402
00:28:01,847 --> 00:28:02,836
Hello? Hold on.

403
00:28:03,648 --> 00:28:05,980
Listen' we planted the bomb
in your shopping centre.

404
00:28:06,518 --> 00:28:08,816
We want $10 million.

405
00:28:09,020 --> 00:28:11,318
Pay up or your...
other properties will get bombed.

406
00:28:11,823 --> 00:28:12,812
Let me talk to him.

407
00:28:13,091 --> 00:28:14,922
All right.

408
00:28:15,527 --> 00:28:16,721
But it's a huge amount of money.

409
00:28:17,295 --> 00:28:19,092
We'll need to call a board meeting.

410
00:28:19,297 --> 00:28:20,559
You've got 24 hours.

411
00:28:20,966 --> 00:28:22,024
Don't call the police.

412
00:28:24,169 --> 00:28:25,158
What to do then?

413
00:28:25,337 --> 00:28:27,567
Must be some hoax.

414
00:28:27,973 --> 00:28:28,962
Yes.

415
00:28:29,074 --> 00:28:30,371
So what do we do?

416
00:28:30,542 --> 00:28:31,531
Call the police.

417
00:28:31,743 --> 00:28:32,732
We pay so much tax.

418
00:28:32,978 --> 00:28:34,275
The police should do something for us.

419
00:28:35,747 --> 00:28:36,771
Call the head for me.

420
00:28:36,848 --> 00:28:37,837
Yes.

421
00:28:37,883 --> 00:28:39,748
Raymond' you were extremely lucky.

422
00:28:40,018 --> 00:28:43,283
lt's amazing that no one
was hurt in the explosion.

423
00:28:43,555 --> 00:28:44,920
Thank God for that.

424
00:28:46,358 --> 00:28:48,223
And the Chu case' well done!

425
00:28:48,460 --> 00:28:50,223
Thank you. But it wasn't just me.

426
00:28:50,896 --> 00:28:51,885
That's right.

427
00:28:51,930 --> 00:28:53,124
You've proved yourself.

428
00:28:53,398 --> 00:28:56,299
You should handle this case. Do you agree?

429
00:28:57,569 --> 00:28:58,900
Sure. Of course.

430
00:29:00,539 --> 00:29:01,528
Bill.

431
00:29:02,441 --> 00:29:03,999
This is a very tough case.

432
00:29:04,376 --> 00:29:06,071
That's why they gave it to us.

433
00:29:06,645 --> 00:29:09,443
ln our department'
who do you think can solve it?

434
00:29:10,515 --> 00:29:11,777
You're the only one.

435
00:29:12,217 --> 00:29:13,206
l want a better idea.

436
00:29:13,985 --> 00:29:15,316
And it's definitely not me.

437
00:29:16,254 --> 00:29:19,223
Maybe we could bring back
somebody who's on leave.

438
00:29:20,592 --> 00:29:21,684
Do you mean somebody like Ka-kui?

439
00:29:22,294 --> 00:29:23,283
He has good experience.

440
00:29:23,495 --> 00:29:26,931
l don't know.
He's unorthodox' impulsive.

441
00:29:27,265 --> 00:29:29,256
He'll only give us trouble.
We have to bear the consquence

442
00:29:29,534 --> 00:29:32,503
l agree he's a little bit rash'
but underneath he's a good cop.

443
00:29:33,472 --> 00:29:34,461
l won't let him do it.

444
00:29:34,606 --> 00:29:36,972
But if you think he's our man'
you go find him.

445
00:29:45,150 --> 00:29:46,242
Let's see who's the boss.

446
00:29:57,329 --> 00:29:58,318
Over there.

447
00:29:58,363 --> 00:29:59,352
Here?

448
00:30:08,273 --> 00:30:09,262
Fasten your seat belt please.

449
00:30:10,342 --> 00:30:11,832
l forgot the sun screen...

450
00:30:12,010 --> 00:30:13,170
Buy it when we get there.

451
00:30:15,714 --> 00:30:17,181
Did you get your passport?
When you were young?

452
00:30:18,183 --> 00:30:20,708
Put out a call
for Detective Chan Ka-kui.

453
00:30:20,886 --> 00:30:21,875
Sure.

454
00:30:23,555 --> 00:30:24,715
Attention please.

455
00:30:25,123 --> 00:30:26,556
Will Chan Ka-kui....

456
00:30:26,591 --> 00:30:28,115
Let me see.
No' don't look!

457
00:30:28,159 --> 00:30:30,024
lt's cute.
lt's horrible.

458
00:30:30,462 --> 00:30:32,430
..Ka-kui please contact us.

459
00:30:32,464 --> 00:30:33,431
That's you. Yeah.

460
00:30:33,465 --> 00:30:35,057
What's up?
l don't know.

461
00:30:35,100 --> 00:30:36,226
l won't be long.

462
00:30:39,437 --> 00:30:41,029
Are you Mr Chan?
Yeah.

463
00:30:41,072 --> 00:30:43,233
l'm afraid there seems to be

464
00:30:43,441 --> 00:30:44,533
a problem with your passport.

465
00:30:45,110 --> 00:30:46,099
Really?

466
00:30:46,311 --> 00:30:47,505
lt'll just be a quick check.

467
00:30:49,581 --> 00:30:50,570
What's going on?

468
00:30:51,816 --> 00:30:53,306
l'll be back right away.

469
00:30:53,952 --> 00:30:54,941
Hurry!

470
00:30:55,220 --> 00:30:56,209
OK

471
00:30:57,789 --> 00:30:58,778
Bye-bye.

472
00:31:11,469 --> 00:31:12,458
What do you want?

473
00:31:13,138 --> 00:31:15,003
Thank you.
You're welcome.

474
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:16,132
What is it? l have a plane waiting.

475
00:31:17,108 --> 00:31:18,234
We have a problem.

476
00:31:18,577 --> 00:31:22,138
lt seems that the bombing case
has become a blackmail case.

477
00:31:22,514 --> 00:31:23,947
And it's a very tough one.

478
00:31:23,982 --> 00:31:24,914
So?

479
00:31:24,950 --> 00:31:26,713
This case is a real challenge.

480
00:31:27,018 --> 00:31:28,007
Raymond was hoping...

481
00:31:29,354 --> 00:31:31,618
l was hoping that you might
cancel your holiday.

482
00:31:32,657 --> 00:31:34,522
No! l've already boarded the plane.

483
00:31:35,226 --> 00:31:36,386
And l've quit.

484
00:31:36,561 --> 00:31:37,550
l know how you feel.

485
00:31:38,029 --> 00:31:39,826
You've been under pressure lately.

486
00:31:40,231 --> 00:31:41,323
But ducking out like this?

487
00:31:41,700 --> 00:31:42,689
l'm not ducking out.

488
00:31:43,168 --> 00:31:44,692
He said he's not ducking out!

489
00:31:47,305 --> 00:31:50,399
Raymond is a great admirer of your abilities.

490
00:31:52,043 --> 00:31:54,511
l don't have any abilities.
l'm too impulsive.

491
00:31:55,046 --> 00:31:57,344
lmpulsive? More a man of action.

492
00:31:57,949 --> 00:31:59,974
lf only l could control my actions.

493
00:32:00,251 --> 00:32:02,742
A true man of action
is one who acts upon instinct.

494
00:32:03,722 --> 00:32:05,952
l think the police force

495
00:32:06,124 --> 00:32:07,113
needs men with discipline.

496
00:32:07,258 --> 00:32:09,158
lnstinctive men have to be unconventional'

497
00:32:09,594 --> 00:32:11,391
even at the cost of discipline.

498
00:32:11,763 --> 00:32:15,494
lf you did everything by the book'
no cases would be solved. Am l right?

499
00:32:16,034 --> 00:32:17,023
Absolutely.

500
00:32:18,770 --> 00:32:19,759
l'd better get back on board.

501
00:32:22,207 --> 00:32:23,196
You're right.

502
00:32:23,942 --> 00:32:24,931
Goodbye.

503
00:32:29,748 --> 00:32:30,737
How much is the ransom?

504
00:32:30,815 --> 00:32:33,113
Ten million. That's all we know.

505
00:32:33,385 --> 00:32:34,374
Do we have any suspects?

506
00:32:34,853 --> 00:32:35,842
Not a clue.

507
00:32:36,588 --> 00:32:38,647
Do you think these people are insane?

508
00:32:39,224 --> 00:32:40,953
Why are you asking me? l don't know.

509
00:32:42,527 --> 00:32:44,392
Have you traced the dynamite?

510
00:32:44,562 --> 00:32:45,927
Why?

511
00:32:46,197 --> 00:32:47,186
Yes. Why?

512
00:32:47,232 --> 00:32:48,221
Simple.

513
00:32:48,266 --> 00:32:50,700
Dynamite is a controlled substance.

514
00:32:50,935 --> 00:32:53,495
So you either smuggle it in

515
00:32:53,772 --> 00:32:55,262
or steal it from a local company.

516
00:32:55,774 --> 00:32:58,106
He's right. We'd not thought of that.

517
00:32:58,510 --> 00:32:59,602
We must find their bomb factory

518
00:32:59,878 --> 00:33:02,312
before the company pays the ransom.

519
00:33:02,580 --> 00:33:04,548
lf we do that' we can foil their plans.

520
00:33:05,116 --> 00:33:07,584
Why can you always solve problems
so easily?

521
00:33:07,886 --> 00:33:09,410
You're the one
who's made for this case.

522
00:33:09,587 --> 00:33:10,849
You're in charge.

523
00:33:13,825 --> 00:33:14,814
l've got a plane to catch.

524
00:33:16,194 --> 00:33:18,822
Wait! Ka-kui.

525
00:33:18,963 --> 00:33:19,952
You can go there any time.

526
00:33:19,998 --> 00:33:22,023
This case is a one-off.

527
00:33:22,634 --> 00:33:23,623
Go there next time. OK?

528
00:33:25,837 --> 00:33:27,099
l'd better talk to May first.

529
00:33:27,472 --> 00:33:28,461
Hurry up' then.

530
00:33:33,945 --> 00:33:34,934
Hurry up.

531
00:33:35,947 --> 00:33:37,574
Miss!
Yes' sir?

532
00:33:37,615 --> 00:33:39,276
My plane...
lt just took off.

533
00:33:42,320 --> 00:33:43,309
lt's taken off!

534
00:33:44,022 --> 00:33:45,853
You've missed your flight!

535
00:33:46,057 --> 00:33:47,820
Trust them to be on schedule.

536
00:33:48,993 --> 00:33:50,790
l still have May's passport.

537
00:33:51,096 --> 00:33:54,224
Damn! lt sure isn't your lucky day!

538
00:33:56,735 --> 00:33:57,724
Now what?

539
00:34:07,946 --> 00:34:09,038
Uncle Bill' we better go.

540
00:34:11,282 --> 00:34:12,271
All right?

541
00:34:12,317 --> 00:34:13,306
l ate something bad.

542
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:16,509
That way' sir.

543
00:34:16,554 --> 00:34:17,543
Thank you.

544
00:34:17,922 --> 00:34:21,358
Excuse me. We're police officers.
We're here to see Miss Wong.

545
00:34:21,693 --> 00:34:22,682
