821
00:54:38,342 --> 00:54:39,866
l think l've got a suspect.

822
00:54:40,043 --> 00:54:41,635
Be careful. He's very dangerous.

823
00:54:41,878 --> 00:54:43,470
He could be armed.

824
00:54:43,947 --> 00:54:45,107
Keep everything low key.

825
00:54:54,925 --> 00:54:58,417
Excuse me' you're supposed to use
the pedestrian crossing.

826
00:54:59,930 --> 00:55:00,919
Go on.

827
00:55:01,365 --> 00:55:02,662
Give me a chance' Officer.

828
00:55:03,233 --> 00:55:04,222
Can l see your lD card?

829
00:55:16,713 --> 00:55:17,702
Calling HQ...

830
00:55:19,883 --> 00:55:29,554
PC 12674' can you hear...

831
00:55:36,233 --> 00:55:39,396
An officer needs assistance
in Ting Kok Road.

832
00:55:43,573 --> 00:55:44,870
l'm sorry' he isn't here.

833
00:55:45,575 --> 00:55:46,564
Don't be sorry.

834
00:55:47,577 --> 00:55:49,909
lt's the way things go.
lt wasn't your fault.

835
00:55:51,381 --> 00:55:52,609
How long have you been in uniform?

836
00:55:52,883 --> 00:55:54,316
About two months.

837
00:55:55,685 --> 00:55:56,743
Then you're excused.

838
00:55:57,020 --> 00:55:59,682
Will l get in trouble
for losing my gun?

839
00:56:00,190 --> 00:56:01,248
What about promotions?!

840
00:56:01,458 --> 00:56:04,325
Don't worry.
As long as you learn

841
00:56:04,494 --> 00:56:06,894
from the experience' it's OK.

842
00:56:07,164 --> 00:56:08,153
lt happens to every cop.

843
00:56:08,198 --> 00:56:09,187
lt won't happen again.

844
00:56:09,332 --> 00:56:10,799
Do you think you'd recognise him?

845
00:56:10,934 --> 00:56:11,923
Sure.

846
00:56:12,069 --> 00:56:13,058
Phone.

847
00:56:13,637 --> 00:56:15,195
l could do with someone like you on the team.

848
00:56:15,572 --> 00:56:16,561
l'll see to it.

849
00:56:18,909 --> 00:56:20,706
Thank you. Can you file this for me?

850
00:56:22,479 --> 00:56:24,310
Hello.
lt's Joker.

851
00:56:24,347 --> 00:56:25,837
Go ahead.
News.

852
00:56:25,882 --> 00:56:26,871
What news?

853
00:56:26,917 --> 00:56:28,578
A guy called Crazy Fai sells dynamite.

854
00:56:28,852 --> 00:56:30,285
Nine o'clock' Hoi Wong Bar.

855
00:56:46,903 --> 00:56:48,564
Do you know what we'll do next?
No.

856
00:56:48,605 --> 00:56:49,594
Really?

857
00:56:55,345 --> 00:56:56,334
What do you want?

858
00:56:56,379 --> 00:56:57,937
Are you Fai? l want to talk.

859
00:56:58,982 --> 00:56:59,971
Do l know you?

860
00:57:00,117 --> 00:57:01,379
No. But you will.

861
00:57:03,520 --> 00:57:04,953
All right. Let's go over there.

862
00:57:06,389 --> 00:57:07,378
l'll be right back.

863
00:57:12,896 --> 00:57:14,830
What's your name?
Lo.

864
00:57:14,865 --> 00:57:15,854
What do you want?

865
00:57:16,166 --> 00:57:17,360
Some explosives.

866
00:57:18,268 --> 00:57:19,257
Explosives?

867
00:57:19,302 --> 00:57:20,530
Do you have some?

868
00:57:20,704 --> 00:57:22,729
What are they for?
Fishing.

869
00:57:24,474 --> 00:57:25,907
You don't look like a fisherman.

870
00:57:26,443 --> 00:57:28,240
What if l told you it was for business?

871
00:57:28,411 --> 00:57:29,400
l'll give you a good price.

872
00:57:29,679 --> 00:57:31,738
What do you say?

873
00:57:34,384 --> 00:57:36,579
All right' l need to speak to someone.

874
00:57:37,020 --> 00:57:38,544
lt's not my stuff.
Don't go away.

875
00:57:39,122 --> 00:57:40,111
Thanks.

876
00:58:01,945 --> 00:58:03,537
Sorry' he's out of stock

877
00:58:03,947 --> 00:58:06,074
but he'll call me back.

878
00:58:06,316 --> 00:58:08,784
Stay here' l'll be back
when l've finished.

879
00:58:08,818 --> 00:58:09,807
Thank you.

880
00:58:55,732 --> 00:58:56,790
Hey' you. Stand up.

881
00:58:58,368 --> 00:58:59,426
What's the matter?

882
00:58:59,469 --> 00:59:01,266
ClD. On your feet.

883
00:59:12,949 --> 00:59:13,938
Hands up.

884
00:59:13,984 --> 00:59:15,144
l only came for a drink.

885
00:59:15,185 --> 00:59:15,879
A drink?

886
00:59:15,919 --> 00:59:17,477
We heard you were dealing contraband.

887
00:59:20,991 --> 00:59:21,980
Eyes front.

888
00:59:30,433 --> 00:59:34,199
Hold it.
Throw me your gun. Quick!

889
00:59:38,908 --> 00:59:39,897
Stand over there.

890
00:59:40,644 --> 00:59:42,441
Easy. Don't do anything stupid.

891
00:59:55,091 --> 00:59:56,524
Come on. Move.

892
00:59:56,860 --> 00:59:58,157
Come out here!

893
01:01:01,558 --> 01:01:02,547
Get lost.

894
01:01:03,360 --> 01:01:07,126
You screwed me over. You bastard!
Why did you call the cops?

895
01:01:10,700 --> 01:01:12,634
Stop! Stop it!

896
01:01:17,574 --> 01:01:20,236
Please' that's enough. Please stop.

897
01:01:21,444 --> 01:01:22,433
Why did you do it?

898
01:01:22,479 --> 01:01:24,140
To make sure you weren't a cop.

899
01:01:24,347 --> 01:01:26,008
That's why l called the cops to prove it.

900
01:01:26,716 --> 01:01:27,978
l can get what you need.

901
01:01:28,551 --> 01:01:29,540
Where is it?

902
01:01:29,686 --> 01:01:30,675
Have you got the money?

903
01:01:36,126 --> 01:01:37,423
lt's cash on delivery.

904
01:01:41,682 --> 01:01:42,671
Keep a look out.

905
01:01:57,799 --> 01:01:58,788
ls it good stuff?

906
01:01:59,066 --> 01:02:00,465
lt's from the quarries.

907
01:02:01,235 --> 01:02:02,224
Got any more?

908
01:02:02,470 --> 01:02:03,459
Yeah' plenty.

909
01:02:11,345 --> 01:02:13,540
There's enough to blow up
the Empire State Building.

910
01:02:14,749 --> 01:02:16,910
l just met him!

911
01:02:17,118 --> 01:02:18,210
l've never seen him before!

912
01:02:22,056 --> 01:02:23,045
Do you think you can get away?


